Edition:
Quote: You may see the Cookee [<i>kuki</i>] or Slave [38] doing that, and throwing it to the Chief or Rangitara [<i>rangatira</i>] or his Wife. [fn] Merely a Maori form of the English `cook'. Polack gives this explanation ... [NZ 2/110-111]. <i>Ibid.</i> 81 A Mourie Slave or Cookee named `(More Prower)' [Mauparaoa] or Carrier of the Whale bone, had stolen a Boat ...
