Date: 0/0/1840
Source: Manners & Customs of the NZers
Author: POLACK
Vol / Page: 1/25fn
Edition:
Quote: The term of Cookee is incorrect for that of a slave; this word is derived from the word cook, an office on board British ships, accounted as only fit for a slave by the New Zealanders - hence the term.
Notes:

